  "prompt": "What does dark humor mean?",
  "response": "Dark humor, also known as black humor or gallows humor, refers to a type of comedy that finds humor in subjects that are generally considered serious, distressing, or taboo. It often involves making light of situations that evoke discomfort, fear, suffering, or death. This kind of humor can be controversial as it may offend some people due to its insensitivity towards serious matters. However, it can also serve as a coping mechanism, allowing people to address and grapple with difficult topics in a less confrontational manner.",
